      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare and macerate",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Grease and line a 23 cm round tin. Toss the sliced {{eating-apples}} with 50 g of the {{caster-sugar}} and leave for 15 minutes. ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Macerating",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaegcck0000zkv4dyobdkfr"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " the slices draws out their juice and softens them so they cook through evenly in the oven.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the remaining 100 g of {{caster-sugar}}, the {{unsalted-butter}}, {{free-range-eggs}}, and {{vanilla-extract}} until smooth. Stir in the {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}}. Fold in the macerated {{eating-apples}} along with all their juice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 40 to 45 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the mixture into the tin. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until the top is golden and a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. The surface will look almost glazed from the apple juices. Leave in the tin for 15 minutes before turning out. Dust with {{icing-sugar}} while still warm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
